explanation: Dynamic programming tracks sequences by last move and score difference. State is (round, last move, diff = Bob - Alice). Transitions iterate over valid next moves (≠ last move) and update diff. Final answer sums sequences where diff > 0. Complexity is quadratic due to diff range.

